09:06.458 --> 09:10.245
I broke many laws
putting you on my team,

09:10.245 --> 09:14.466
but no one
can find out about us.

09:14.466 --> 09:16.164
Is that clear?

09:21.561 --> 09:24.868
Automated voice:
<i>All personnel required
in the mess hall on C Deck.</i>

09:24.868 --> 09:27.828
<i>All personnel.
No exceptions.</i>

09:27.828 --> 09:31.266
<i>All personnel required
in the mess hall of C Deck.</i>

09:31.266 --> 09:33.834
<i>All personnel.
No exceptions.</i>

09:36.184 --> 09:38.273
Sorry, sorry.

09:41.668 --> 09:43.887
Hey, mind if I sit here?

09:43.887 --> 09:47.151
Sure. I'’m Alicia Nevins.
Some people call me Ali.

09:47.151 --> 09:49.066
Not that that'’s a preference.
It just kinda happens.

09:49.066 --> 09:51.591
Oh, I'’m on
the waste management team.
I-- I know. Gross.

09:51.591 --> 09:52.983
But it'’s not like
I didn'’t apply

09:52.983 --> 09:54.245
to every other branch
on the ship first.

09:54.245 --> 09:55.769
But, hey,
it got me on the ship.

09:55.769 --> 09:56.987
And my family are actually
really supportive.

09:56.987 --> 09:58.293
But why wouldn'’t they be, right?

09:58.293 --> 09:59.773
If we actually succeed
in building

09:59.773 --> 10:01.339
a sustainable colony,
all of our families

10:01.339 --> 10:03.472
get to be the first to
come out and settle there.

10:03.472 --> 10:06.127
Um, who are you?

10:06.127 --> 10:08.956
Call me Angus.
In horticulture.

10:08.956 --> 10:11.349
Wait, I know you.
You'’re that farmer boy.

10:11.349 --> 10:12.612
You grew crops
